      "markdown": "# Example6-S Solution \n\nNote that $v(0)=C.$ But we are given that $v(0)=-6$ ,So $C=-6$ and \n\n\n\n$$v(t)=3t^{2}+4t-6$$\n\nSince $v(t)=s^{\\prime}(t)$ ,s is the antiderivative of v:\n\n$$s(t)=3\\frac{t^{3}}{3}+4\\frac{t^{2}}{2}-6t+D=t^{3}+2t^{2}-6t+D $$\n\nThis gives $s(0)=D$ We are given that $s(0)=9,\\quad\\forall D=9$ and the required position function is \n\n$$s(t)=t^{3}+2t^{2}-6t+9$$",
